UNITED STATES of America, Appellant, v. Aubrey HARBOUR, Appellee. No. 7187. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Jan. 12, 1934. Allen Crenshaw, Atty. Dept, of Justice, of Jackson, Miss., and E. J. Currie, Asst. U. S. Atty., of Meridian, Miss., for the United States. B. B. McClendon, of Jackson, Miss., for appellee.

Before BRYAN, SIBLEY, and HUTCHESON, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment is affirmed.
